Class ZMQOutputListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.picslurper.output.ZMQOutputListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OutputListener

    public class ZMQOutputListener
extends Object
implements OutputListener
    Using ZeroMQ (because it is awesome and I wanted to learn it so fuck off) we set up a subscription based server which tells anyone listening about any new images. The name of the queue can be specified
    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • newImageDownloaded

        public void newImageDownloaded(WriteableImageOutput written)
        Description copied from interface: OutputListener
        Called for each image successfully downloaded. This function is told about the status which generated the image, the url from which the image was eventually downloaded (after various redirects) and the output file. The StatusConsumption instance from the StatusConsumer that processed the status is also provided
